body.text: This takes two locations and returns the distance between them, taking into account the curve of the earth (assuming a perfectly spherical earth).  Yes, this is making things harder than necessary but allows for future expansion.
Note that this equation takes in lat/lon in decimal degrees and returns a value in nm, which is then converted to statute miles.
Split out lat/lon from the locations.
I can't remember why I put the rounding in to be honest.
Now set up some variables that will make things easier later.
Now square a and b.  (I'm skipping d as a variable name so its not mistaken for distance.)
Now convert from radians to nm
To test this script manually set Location1 to 33.95, 118.4 and Location2 to 40.633333, 73.783333.  The distance in radians should equal 0.623585 and in nm equals 2144 (2143 and change is OK).
Now ask yourself why you did it the hard way.
